 <title>Recommended Hardware Minimums for an Entry-scale ESX, KVM with Dedicated Cluster for Metering, Monitoring, and Logging</title>
 <para>
  These recommended minimums are based on example configurations included with
  the installation models (see <xref linkend="example-configurations"/>). They
  are suitable only for demo environments. For production systems you will want
  to consider your capacity and performance requirements when making decisions
  about your hardware.
 </para>
 <para>
  &productname; currently supports the following ESXi versions:
 </para>
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    ESXi version 6.0
   </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    ESXi version 6.0 (Update 1b)
   </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    ESXi version 6.5
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
 <para>
  The following are the requirements for your vCenter server:
 </para>
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    Software: vCenter (It is recommended to run the same
    server version as the ESXi hosts.)
   </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    License Requirements: vSphere Enterprise Plus license
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
